dataset_description.json.Name: SONG dataset
Funding: Institute for Basic Science Grant IBS R015-D1
National Research Foundation of Korea NRF-2019M3E5D2A01060299 and NRF-2019R1A2C1085566

trial_type.LongName: Gradual-onset continuous performance task with face stimuli
trial_type.Description: This is a minimally preprocessed output file. The experiment was run by Matlab and Psychtoolbox.

Levels.onset: the onset of the first trial is recorded
Levels.duration: trial duration (1 s); a trial consists of transition (0.8 s) and intact (0.2 s) stimulus presentations
Levels.image_id: 11 unique faces in total; images 1-10 are nontarget faces and image 11 is a target face
Levels.transition_duration: upon the onset of the trial, the stimulus from the previous trial gradually transitioned to the stimulus from the current trial in a linear pixel-by-pixel interpolation
Levels.resp_1st: (1) button press recorded, (0) no button press recorded
Levels.resp_2nd: (1) in case where two button presses are recorded in a trial
Levels.rt_1st: the response time of the 1st button press
Levels.rt_2nd: the response time of the 2nd button press
Levels.acc: (1) hit and correct rejection, (0) false alarm and miss

trial_type.LongName: Gradual-onset continuous performance task with scene stimuli
trial_type.Description: This is a minimally preprocessed output file. The experiment was run by Matlab and Psychtoolbox.

Levels.onset: the onset of the first trial is recorded
Levels.duration: trial duration (1.2 s); a trial consists of transition (0.5 s) and intact (0.7 s) stimulus presentations
Levels.target_nontarget: (1) indoor, (2) outdoor; whether the indoor or outdoor scenes corresponded to the target/nontarget category was counterbalanced across participants
Levels.image_id: unique 360 scene images (no repeats of the same image)
Levels.transition_duration: upon the onset of the trial, the stimulus from the previous trial gradually transitioned to the stimulus from the current trial in a linear pixel-by-pixel interpolation
Levels.resp_1st: (1) indoor button press, (2) outdoor button press, (0) no button press recorded
Levels.resp_2nd: (1 or 2) in case where two button presses are recorded in a trial
Levels.rt_1st: the response time of the 1st button press
Levels.rt_2nd: the response time of the 2nd button press
Levels.acc: (1) hit and correct rejection, (0) false alarm and miss

README:
Large-scale neural dynamics in a shared low-dimensional state space reflect cognitive and attentional dynamics. Hayoung Song, Won Mok Shim, Monica D. Rosenberg.

Raw functional MRI data of the SitcOm, Nature documentary, Gradual-onset continuous performance task (SONG) dataset is available here. The associated behavioral data, processed fMRI output, and main analysis codes are published in Github [https://github.com/hyssong/neuraldynamics]. For additional inquiries, please contact Hayoung Song (hyssong@uchicago.edu).
